2026-04-02 | Paint Fence (No More Than Two Adjacent Same Color)

	Question
Return total number of valid ways to paint the fence.

	Approach
We track two cases:

1.	same:
		last two posts have same color  
2.	diff:
		last two posts have different colors  

Transitions:
- If same:
		we must paint next different  
- If diff:
		we can paint same or different  

Recurrence:
- same[i] = diff[i-1]  
- diff[i] = (same[i-1] + diff[i-1]) * (k-1)

Total:
		total[i] = same[i] + diff[i]

Base cases:
- n = 1 → k  
- n = 2 → k + k*(k-1) = k²  

Optimized:
		f[i] = (f[i-1] + f[i-2]) * (k-1)

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int countWays(int n, int k) {

        if(n == 1) return k;

        int prev2 = k;        // f[1]
        int prev1 = k * k;    // f[2]

        for(int i = 3; i <= n; i++){
            int curr = (prev1 + prev2) * (k - 1);
            prev2 = prev1;
            prev1 = curr;
        }

        return prev1;
    }
};

	Key Insight
We track whether last two posts are same or different.  
This leads to a **Fibonacci-like recurrence**:

		f[n] = (f[n-1] + f[n-2]) × (k-1)

This efficiently counts all valid configurations.
